       <h2>About BookerT</h2><br>
       <p style="font-size:24px">
       	BookerT was founded to try to close the equity gap in higher education faced by many first-generation college students. 
       </p>
       <p style="font-size:24px">
        First-generation college students at institutions of higher learning often do not receive the support they need to excel (ie. to thrive, not just survive). BookerT aims to address the lack of funding for professional development, unpaid internships, and family emergencies by leveraging the power of the personal network and crowdfunding in order to subsidize the cost of items normally prohibitively unaffordable to the average first-generation college student. Usually these items include professional attire, plane tickets to conferences, rent and groceries for unpaid summer internships, and general family emergency packages for unexpected medical emergencies, evictions, and other serious and personal events.
        <br><br>
        By working together with financial aid offices and scholarship programs in colleges all across America, BookerT will augment the impact of existing resources and give first-generation college students the agency to take more control over their academic and extracurricular lives.
       </p>
